6781  private:
6782  template <typename TSlot>
6783  V8_INLINE void MarkPointersImpl(TSlot start, TSlot end) {
6784  // Treat weak references as strong.
6785  for (TSlot p = start; p < end; ++p) {
6786  typename TSlot::TObject object = p.load(cage_base());
6787 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DIRECT_HANDLE
6788  if (object.ptr() == kTaggedNullAddress) continue;
6789 #endif
6790  Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
6791  if (object.GetHeapObject(&heap_object)) {
6792  MarkHeapObject(heap_object);
6793  }
6794  }
6795  }
6796 
6797  V8_INLINE void MarkHeapObject(Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object) {
6798  if (filter_->MarkAsReachable(heap_object)) {
6799  marking_stack_.push_back(heap_object);
6800  }
6801  }
6802 
6803  UnreachableObjectsFilter* filter_;
6804  std::vector<Tagged<HeapObject>> marking_stack_;
6805  };
6806 
6807  friend class MarkingVisitor;
6808 
6809  void MarkReachableObjects() {
6810  MarkingVisitor visitor(this);
6811  heap_->stack().SetMarkerIfNeededAndCallback(
6812  [this, &visitor]() { heap_->IterateRoots(&visitor, {}); });
6813  visitor.TransitiveClosure();
6814  }
6815 
6816  Heap* heap_;
6817  DISALLOW_GARBAGE_COLLECTION(no_gc_)
6818  std::unordered_map<MemoryChunkMetadata*, std::unique_ptr<BucketType>,
6819  base::hash<MemoryChunkMetadata*>>
6820  reachable_;
6821 };
6822 
6823 HeapObjectIterator::HeapObjectIterator(
6824  Heap* heap, HeapObjectIterator::HeapObjectsFiltering filtering)
6825  : HeapObjectIterator(
6826  heap,
6827  new SafepointScope(heap->isolate(),
6828  kGlobalSafepointForSharedSpaceIsolate),
6829  filtering) {}
6830 
6831 HeapObjectIterator::HeapObjectIterator(Heap* heap,
6832  const SafepointScope& safepoint_scope,
6833  HeapObjectsFiltering filtering)
6834  : HeapObjectIterator(heap, nullptr, filtering) {}
6835 
6836 HeapObjectIterator::HeapObjectIterator(
6837  Heap* heap, SafepointScope* safepoint_scope_or_nullptr,
6838  HeapObjectsFiltering filtering)
6839  : heap_(heap),
6840  safepoint_scope_(safepoint_scope_or_nullptr),
6841  space_iterator_(heap_) {
6842  heap_->MakeHeapIterable();
6843  switch (filtering) {
6844  case kFilterUnreachable:
6845  filter_ = std::make_unique<UnreachableObjectsFilter>(heap_);
6846  break;
6847  default:
6848  break;
6849  }
6850  // Start the iteration.
6851  CHECK(space_iterator_.HasNext());
6852  object_iterator_ = space_iterator_.Next()->GetObjectIterator(heap_);
6853 }
6854 
6855 HeapObjectIterator::~HeapObjectIterator() = default;
6856 
6857 Tagged<HeapObject> HeapObjectIterator::Next() {
6858  if (!filter_) return NextObject();
6859 
6860  Tagged<HeapObject> obj = NextObject();
6861  while (!obj.is_null() && filter_->SkipObject(obj)) obj = NextObject();
6862  return obj;
6863 }
6864 
6865 Tagged<HeapObject> HeapObjectIterator::NextObject() {
6866  // No iterator means we are done.
6867  if (!object_iterator_) return Tagged<HeapObject>();
6868 
6869  Tagged<HeapObject> obj = object_iterator_->Next();
6870  // If the current iterator has more objects we are fine.
6871  if (!obj.is_null()) return obj;
6872  // Go though the spaces looking for one that has objects.
6873  while (space_iterator_.HasNext()) {
6874  object_iterator_ = space_iterator_.Next()->GetObjectIterator(heap_);
6875  obj = object_iterator_->Next();
6876  if (!obj.is_null()) return obj;
6877  }
6878  // Done with the last space.
6879  object_iterator_.reset();
6880  return Tagged<HeapObject>();
6881 }

6883 void Heap::UpdateTotalGCTime(base::TimeDelta duration) {

6885 }
6886 
6887 void Heap::ExternalStringTable::CleanUpYoung() {
6888  int last = 0;
6889  Isolate* isolate = heap_->isolate();
6890  for (size_t i = 0; i < young_strings_.size(); ++i) {
6891  Tagged<Object> o = young_strings_[i];
6892  if (IsTheHole(o, isolate)) {
6893  continue;
6894  }
6895  // The real external string is already in one of these vectors and was or
6896  // will be processed. Re-processing it will add a duplicate to the vector.
6897  if (IsThinString(o)) continue;
6898  DCHECK(IsExternalString(o));
6899  if (HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(o)) {
6900  young_strings_[last++] = o;
6901  } else {
6902  old_strings_.push_back(o);
6903  }
6904  }
6905  young_strings_.resize(last);
6906 }
6907 
6908 void Heap::ExternalStringTable::CleanUpAll() {
6909  CleanUpYoung();
6910  int last = 0;
6911  Isolate* isolate = heap_->isolate();
6912  for (size_t i = 0; i < old_strings_.size(); ++i) {
6913  Tagged<Object> o = old_strings_[i];
6914  if (IsTheHole(o, isolate)) {
6915  continue;
6916  }
6917  // The real external string is already in one of these vectors and was or
6918  // will be processed. Re-processing it will add a duplicate to the vector.
6919  if (IsThinString(o)) continue;
6920  DCHECK(IsExternalString(o));
6921  DCHECK(!HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(o));
6922  old_strings_[last++] = o;
6923  }
6924  old_strings_.resize(last);
6925  if (v8_flags.verify_heap) {
6926  Verify();
6927  }
6928 }
6929 
6930 void Heap::ExternalStringTable::TearDown() {
6931  for (size_t i = 0; i < young_strings_.size(); ++i) {
6932  Tagged<Object> o = young_strings_[i];
6933  // Dont finalize thin strings.
6934  if (IsThinString(o)) continue;
6935  heap_->FinalizeExternalString(Cast<ExternalString>(o));
6936  }
6937  young_strings_.clear();
6938  for (size_t i = 0; i < old_strings_.size(); ++i) {
6939  Tagged<Object> o = old_strings_[i];
6940  // Dont finalize thin strings.
6941  if (IsThinString(o)) continue;
6942  heap_->FinalizeExternalString(Cast<ExternalString>(o));
6943  }
6944  old_strings_.clear();
6945 }

6947 void Heap::RememberUnmappedPage(Address page, bool compacted) {
6948  // Tag the page pointer to make it findable in the dump file.
6949  if (compacted) {
6950  page ^= 0xC1EAD & (PageMetadata::kPageSize - 1); // Cleared.
6951  } else {
6952  page ^= 0x1D1ED & (PageMetadata::kPageSize - 1); // I died.
6953  }
6954  remembered_unmapped_pages_[remembered_unmapped_pages_index_] = page;
6955  remembered_unmapped_pages_index_++;
6956  remembered_unmapped_pages_index_ %= kRememberedUnmappedPages;
6957 }

6976 StrongRootsEntry* Heap::RegisterStrongRoots(const char* label,
6977  FullObjectSlot start,
6978  FullObjectSlot end) {
6979  // We're either on the main thread, or in a background thread with an active
6980  // local heap.
6981  DCHECK(isolate()->CurrentLocalHeap()->IsRunning());
6982 
6983  base::MutexGuard guard(&strong_roots_mutex_);
6984 
6985  StrongRootsEntry* entry = new StrongRootsEntry(label);
6986  entry->start = start;
6987  entry->end = end;
6988  entry->prev = nullptr;
6989  entry->next = strong_roots_head_;
6990 
6991  if (strong_roots_head_) {
6992  DCHECK_NULL(strong_roots_head_->prev);
6993  strong_roots_head_->prev = entry;
6994  }
6995  strong_roots_head_ = entry;
6996 
6997  return entry;
6998 }
6999 
7000 void Heap::UpdateStrongRoots(StrongRootsEntry* entry, FullObjectSlot start,
7001  FullObjectSlot end) {
7002  entry->start = start;
7003  entry->end = end;
7004 }
7005 
7006 void Heap::UnregisterStrongRoots(StrongRootsEntry* entry) {
7007  // We're either on the main thread, or in a background thread with an active
7008  // local heap.
7009  DCHECK(isolate()->CurrentLocalHeap()->IsRunning());
7010 
7011  base::MutexGuard guard(&strong_roots_mutex_);
7012 
7013  StrongRootsEntry* prev = entry->prev;
7014  StrongRootsEntry* next = entry->next;
7015 
7016  if (prev) prev->next = next;
7017  if (next) next->prev = prev;
7018 
7019  if (strong_roots_head_ == entry) {
7020  DCHECK_NULL(prev);
7021  strong_roots_head_ = next;
7022  }
7023 
7024  delete entry;
7025 }

7039 void Heap::PostFinalizationRegistryCleanupTaskIfNeeded() {
7040  // Only one cleanup task is posted at a time.
7041  if (!HasDirtyJSFinalizationRegistries() ||
7042  is_finalization_registry_cleanup_task_posted_) {
7043  return;
7044  }
7045  auto task = std::make_unique<FinalizationRegistryCleanupTask>(this);
7046  task_runner_->PostNonNestableTask(std::move(task));
7047  is_finalization_registry_cleanup_task_posted_ = true;
7048 }
7049 
7050 void Heap::EnqueueDirtyJSFinalizationRegistry(
7051  Tagged<JSFinalizationRegistry> finalization_registry,
7052  std::function<void(Tagged<HeapObject> object, ObjectSlot slot,
7053  Tagged<Object> target)>
7054  gc_notify_updated_slot) {
7055  // Add a FinalizationRegistry to the tail of the dirty list.
7056  DCHECK(!HasDirtyJSFinalizationRegistries() ||
7057  IsJSFinalizationRegistry(dirty_js_finalization_registries_list()));
7058  DCHECK(IsUndefined(finalization_registry->next_dirty(), isolate()));
7059  DCHECK(!finalization_registry->scheduled_for_cleanup());
7060  finalization_registry->set_scheduled_for_cleanup(true);
7061  if (IsUndefined(dirty_js_finalization_registries_list_tail(), isolate())) {
7062  DCHECK(IsUndefined(dirty_js_finalization_registries_list(), isolate()));
7063  set_dirty_js_finalization_registries_list(finalization_registry);
7064  // dirty_js_finalization_registries_list_ is rescanned by
7065  // ProcessWeakListRoots.
7066  } else {
7067  Tagged<JSFinalizationRegistry> tail = Cast<JSFinalizationRegistry>(
7068  dirty_js_finalization_registries_list_tail());
7069  tail->set_next_dirty(finalization_registry);
7070  gc_notify_updated_slot(
7071  tail, tail->RawField(JSFinalizationRegistry::kNextDirtyOffset),
7072  finalization_registry);
7073  }
7074  set_dirty_js_finalization_registries_list_tail(finalization_registry);
7075  // dirty_js_finalization_registries_list_tail_ is rescanned by
7076  // ProcessWeakListRoots.
7077 }
7078 
7079 MaybeDirectHandle<JSFinalizationRegistry>
7080 Heap::DequeueDirtyJSFinalizationRegistry() {
7081  // Take a FinalizationRegistry from the head of the dirty list for fairness.
7082  if (HasDirtyJSFinalizationRegistries()) {
7083  DirectHandle<JSFinalizationRegistry> head(
7084  Cast<JSFinalizationRegistry>(dirty_js_finalization_registries_list()),
7085  isolate());
7086  set_dirty_js_finalization_registries_list(head->next_dirty());
7087  head->set_next_dirty(ReadOnlyRoots(this).undefined_value());
7088  if (*head == dirty_js_finalization_registries_list_tail()) {
7089  set_dirty_js_finalization_registries_list_tail(
7090  ReadOnlyRoots(this).undefined_value());
7091  }
7092  return head;
7093  }
7094  return {};
7095 }
7096 
7097 void Heap::RemoveDirtyFinalizationRegistriesOnContext(
7098  Tagged<NativeContext> context) {
7099  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
7100 
7101  Isolate* isolate = this->isolate();
7102  Tagged<Object> prev = ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).undefined_value();
7103  Tagged<Object> current = dirty_js_finalization_registries_list();
7104  while (!IsUndefined(current, isolate)) {
7105  Tagged<JSFinalizationRegistry> finalization_registry =
7106  Cast<JSFinalizationRegistry>(current);
7107  if (finalization_registry->native_context() == context) {
7108  if (IsUndefined(prev, isolate)) {
7109  set_dirty_js_finalization_registries_list(
7110  finalization_registry->next_dirty());
7111  } else {
7112  Cast<JSFinalizationRegistry>(prev)->set_next_dirty(
7113  finalization_registry->next_dirty());
7114  }
7115  finalization_registry->set_scheduled_for_cleanup(false);
7116  current = finalization_registry->next_dirty();
7117  finalization_registry->set_next_dirty(
7118  ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).undefined_value());
7119  } else {
7120  prev = current;
7121  current = finalization_registry->next_dirty();
7122  }
7123  }
7124  set_dirty_js_finalization_registries_list_tail(prev);
7125 }

7127 void Heap::KeepDuringJob(DirectHandle<HeapObject> target) {
7128  DCHECK(IsUndefined(weak_refs_keep_during_job()) ||
7129  IsOrderedHashSet(weak_refs_keep_during_job()));
7130  Handle<OrderedHashSet> table;
7131  if (IsUndefined(weak_refs_keep_during_job(), isolate())) {
7132  table = isolate()->factory()->NewOrderedHashSet();
7133  } else {
7134  table =
7135  handle(Cast<OrderedHashSet>(weak_refs_keep_during_job()), isolate());
7136  }
7137  MaybeHandle<OrderedHashSet> maybe_table =
7138  OrderedHashSet::Add(isolate(), table, target);
7139  if (!maybe_table.ToHandle(&table)) {
7140  FatalProcessOutOfMemory(
7141  "Fatal JavaScript error: Too many distinct WeakRef objects "
7142  "created or dereferenced during single event loop turn.");
7143  }
7144  set_weak_refs_keep_during_job(*table);
7145 }

7167 bool Heap::GetObjectTypeName(size_t index, const char** object_type,
7168  const char** object_sub_type) {
7169  if (index >= ObjectStats::OBJECT_STATS_COUNT) return false;
7170 
7171  switch (static_cast<int>(index)) {
7172 #define COMPARE_AND_RETURN_NAME(name) \
7173  case name: \
7174  *object_type = #name; \
7175  *object_sub_type = ""; \
7176  return true;
7177  INSTANCE_TYPE_LIST(COMPARE_AND_RETURN_NAME)
7178 #undef COMPARE_AND_RETURN_NAME
7179 
7180 #define COMPARE_AND_RETURN_NAME(name) \
7181  case ObjectStats::FIRST_VIRTUAL_TYPE + \
7182  static_cast<int>(ObjectStats::VirtualInstanceType::name): \
7183  *object_type = #name; \
7184  *object_sub_type = ""; \
7185  return true;
7186  VIRTUAL_INSTANCE_TYPE_LIST(COMPARE_AND_RETURN_NAME)
7187 #undef COMPARE_AND_RETURN_NAME
7188  }
7189  return false;
7190 }

7229 
7230 bool Heap::AllowedToBeMigrated(Tagged<Map> map, Tagged<HeapObject> object,
7231  AllocationSpace dst) {
7232  // Object migration is governed by the following rules:
7233  //
7234  // 1) Objects in new-space can be migrated to the old space
7235  // that matches their target space or they stay in new-space.
7236  // 2) Objects in old-space stay in the same space when migrating.
7237  // 3) Fillers (two or more words) can migrate due to left-trimming of
7238  // fixed arrays in new-space or old space.
7239  // 4) Fillers (one word) can never migrate, they are skipped by
7240  // incremental marking explicitly to prevent invalid pattern.
7241  //
7242  // Since this function is used for debugging only, we do not place
7243  // asserts here, but check everything explicitly.
7244  if (map == ReadOnlyRoots(this).one_pointer_filler_map()) {
7245  return false;
7246  }
7247  InstanceType type = map->instance_type();
7248  MutablePageMetadata* chunk = MutablePageMetadata::FromHeapObject(object);
7249  AllocationSpace src = chunk->owner_identity();
7250  switch (src) {
7251  case NEW_SPACE:
7252  return dst == NEW_SPACE || dst == OLD_SPACE;
7253  case OLD_SPACE:
7254  return dst == OLD_SPACE;
7255  case CODE_SPACE:
7256  return dst == CODE_SPACE && type == INSTRUCTION_STREAM_TYPE;
7257  case SHARED_SPACE:
7258  return dst == SHARED_SPACE;
7259  case TRUSTED_SPACE:
7260  return dst == TRUSTED_SPACE;
7261  case SHARED_TRUSTED_SPACE:
7262  return dst == SHARED_TRUSTED_SPACE;
7263  case LO_SPACE:
7264  case CODE_LO_SPACE:
7265  case NEW_LO_SPACE:
7266  case SHARED_LO_SPACE:
7267  case TRUSTED_LO_SPACE:
7268  case SHARED_TRUSTED_LO_SPACE:
7269  case RO_SPACE:
7270  return false;
7271  }
7272  UNREACHABLE();
7273 }
7274

7277 }

7289 Tagged<Map> Heap::GcSafeMapOfHeapObject(Tagged<HeapObject> object) {

7298 Tagged<GcSafeCode> Heap::GcSafeGetCodeFromInstructionStream(
7299  Tagged<HeapObject> instruction_stream, Address inner_pointer) {
7300  Tagged<InstructionStream> istream =
7301  UncheckedCast<InstructionStream>(instruction_stream);
7302  DCHECK(!istream.is_null());
7303  DCHECK(GcSafeInstructionStreamContains(istream, inner_pointer));
7304  return UncheckedCast<GcSafeCode>(istream->raw_code(kAcquireLoad));
7305 }
7306 
7307 bool Heap::GcSafeInstructionStreamContains(
7308  Tagged<InstructionStream> instruction_stream, Address addr) {
7309  Tagged<Map> map = GcSafeMapOfHeapObject(instruction_stream);
7310  DCHECK_EQ(map, ReadOnlyRoots(this).instruction_stream_map());
7311 
7312  Builtin builtin_lookup_result =
7313  OffHeapInstructionStream::TryLookupCode(isolate(), addr);
7314  if (Builtins::IsBuiltinId(builtin_lookup_result)) {
7315  // Builtins don't have InstructionStream objects.
7316  DCHECK(!Builtins::IsBuiltinId(
7317  instruction_stream->code(kAcquireLoad)->builtin_id()));
7318  return false;
7319  }
7320 
7321  Address start = instruction_stream.address();
7322  Address end = start + instruction_stream->SizeFromMap(map);
7323  return start <= addr && addr < end;
7324 }

7330  if (start.has_value()) {
7331  return UncheckedCast<InstructionStream>(HeapObject::FromAddress(*start));
7332  }
7333

7335 }

7337 std::optional<Tagged<GcSafeCode>> Heap::GcSafeTryFindCodeForInnerPointer(
7338  Address inner_pointer) {
7339  Builtin maybe_builtin =
7340  OffHeapInstructionStream::TryLookupCode(isolate(), inner_pointer);
7341  if (Builtins::IsBuiltinId(maybe_builtin)) {
7342  return Cast<GcSafeCode>(isolate()->builtins()->code(maybe_builtin));
7343  }
7344 
7345  std::optional<Tagged<InstructionStream>> maybe_istream =
7346  GcSafeTryFindInstructionStreamForInnerPointer(inner_pointer);
7347  if (!maybe_istream) return {};
7348 
7349  return GcSafeGetCodeFromInstructionStream(*maybe_istream, inner_pointer);
7350 }

7364 std::optional<Tagged<Code>> Heap::TryFindCodeForInnerPointerForPrinting(
7365  Address inner_pointer) {
7366  if (InSpaceSlow(inner_pointer, i::CODE_SPACE) ||
7367  InSpaceSlow(inner_pointer, i::CODE_LO_SPACE) ||
7368  i::OffHeapInstructionStream::PcIsOffHeap(isolate(), inner_pointer)) {
7369  std::optional<Tagged<GcSafeCode>> maybe_code =
7370  GcSafeTryFindCodeForInnerPointer(inner_pointer);
7371  if (maybe_code.has_value()) {
7372  return maybe_code.value()->UnsafeCastToCode();
7373  }
7374  }
7375  return {};
7376 }

7405 StrongRootAllocatorBase::StrongRootAllocatorBase(LocalHeap* heap)
7406  : StrongRootAllocatorBase(heap->heap()) {}
7407 StrongRootAllocatorBase::StrongRootAllocatorBase(Isolate* isolate)
7408  : StrongRootAllocatorBase(isolate->heap()) {}
7409 StrongRootAllocatorBase::StrongRootAllocatorBase(v8::Isolate* isolate)
7410  : StrongRootAllocatorBase(reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(isolate)) {}
7411 StrongRootAllocatorBase::StrongRootAllocatorBase(LocalIsolate* isolate)
7412  : StrongRootAllocatorBase(isolate->heap()) {}
7413 
7414 // StrongRootBlocks are allocated as a block of addresses, prefixed with a
7415 // StrongRootsEntry pointer:
7416 //
7417 // | StrongRootsEntry*
7418 // | Address 1
7419 // | ...
7420 // | Address N
7421 //
7422 // The allocate method registers the range "Address 1" to "Address N" with the
7423 // heap as a strong root array, saves that entry in StrongRootsEntry*, and
7424 // returns a pointer to Address 1.
7425 Address* StrongRootAllocatorBase::allocate_impl(size_t n) {
7426  void* block = base::Malloc(sizeof(StrongRootsEntry*) + n * sizeof(Address));
7427 
7428  StrongRootsEntry** header = reinterpret_cast<StrongRootsEntry**>(block);
7429  Address* ret = reinterpret_cast<Address*>(reinterpret_cast<char*>(block) +
7430  sizeof(StrongRootsEntry*));
7431 
7432  memset(ret, kNullAddress, n * sizeof(Address));
7433  *header = heap()->RegisterStrongRoots(
7434  "StrongRootAllocator", FullObjectSlot(ret), FullObjectSlot(ret + n));
7435 
7436  return ret;
7437 }
7438 
7439 void StrongRootAllocatorBase::deallocate_impl(Address* p, size_t n) noexcept {
7440  // The allocate method returns a pointer to Address 1, so the deallocate
7441  // method has to offset that pointer back by sizeof(StrongRootsEntry*).
7442  void* block = reinterpret_cast<char*>(p) - sizeof(StrongRootsEntry*);
7443  StrongRootsEntry** header = reinterpret_cast<StrongRootsEntry**>(block);
7444 
7445  heap()->UnregisterStrongRoots(*header);
7446 
7447  base::Free(block);
7448 }

7456 void Heap::FinishSweepingIfOutOfWork() {
7457  if (sweeper()->major_sweeping_in_progress() &&
7458  sweeper()->UsingMajorSweeperTasks() &&
7459  !sweeper()->AreMajorSweeperTasksRunning()) {
7460  // At this point we know that all concurrent sweeping tasks have run
7461  // out of work and quit: all pages are swept. The main thread still needs
7462  // to complete sweeping though.
7463  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!delay_sweeper_tasks_for_testing_,
7464  !sweeper()->HasUnsweptPagesForMajorSweeping());
7465  EnsureSweepingCompleted(SweepingForcedFinalizationMode::kV8Only);
7466  }
7467  if (cpp_heap()) {
7468  // Ensure that sweeping is also completed for the C++ managed heap, if one
7469  // exists and it's out of work.
7470  CppHeap::From(cpp_heap())->FinishSweepingIfOutOfWork();
7471  }
7472 }
7473 
7474 void Heap::EnsureSweepingCompleted(SweepingForcedFinalizationMode mode) {
7475  CompleteArrayBufferSweeping(this);
7476 
7477  EnsureQuarantinedPagesSweepingCompleted();
7478 
7479  if (sweeper()->sweeping_in_progress()) {
7480  bool was_minor_sweeping_in_progress = minor_sweeping_in_progress();
7481  bool was_major_sweeping_in_progress = major_sweeping_in_progress();
7482  sweeper()->EnsureMajorCompleted();
7483 
7484  if (was_major_sweeping_in_progress) {
7485  TRACE_GC_EPOCH_WITH_FLOW(tracer(), GCTracer::Scope::MC_COMPLETE_SWEEPING,
7486  ThreadKind::kMain,
7487  sweeper_->GetTraceIdForFlowEvent(
7488  GCTracer::Scope::MC_COMPLETE_SWEEPING),
7489  TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_IN);
7490  old_space()->RefillFreeList();
7491  code_space()->RefillFreeList();
7492  if (shared_space()) {
7493  shared_space()->RefillFreeList();
7494  shared_trusted_space()->RefillFreeList();
7495  }
7496 
7497  trusted_space()->RefillFreeList();
7498  } else if (v8_flags.sticky_mark_bits) {
7499  // With sticky markbits there is no separate young gen. Minor sweeping
7500  // will thus sweep pages in old space, so old space freelist should be
7501  // refilled.
7502  DCHECK(was_minor_sweeping_in_progress);
7503  old_space()->RefillFreeList();
7504  }
7505 
7506  if (!v8_flags.sticky_mark_bits && v8_flags.minor_ms && use_new_space() &&
7507  was_minor_sweeping_in_progress) {
7508  TRACE_GC_EPOCH_WITH_FLOW(
7509  tracer(), GCTracer::Scope::MINOR_MS_COMPLETE_SWEEPING,
7510  ThreadKind::kMain,
7511  sweeper_->GetTraceIdForFlowEvent(
7512  GCTracer::Scope::MINOR_MS_COMPLETE_SWEEPING),
7513  TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_IN | TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_OUT);
7514  paged_new_space()->paged_space()->RefillFreeList();
7515  }
7516 
7517  tracer()->NotifyFullSweepingCompletedAndStopCycleIfFinished();
7518 
7519 #ifdef VERIFY_HEAP
7520  if (v8_flags.verify_heap) {
7521  EvacuationVerifier verifier(this);
7522  verifier.Run();
7523  }
7524 #endif
7525  }
7526 
7527  if (mode == SweepingForcedFinalizationMode::kUnifiedHeap && cpp_heap()) {
7528  // Ensure that sweeping is also completed for the C++ managed heap, if one
7529  // exists.
7530  CppHeap::From(cpp_heap())->FinishSweepingIfRunning();
7531  DCHECK(!CppHeap::From(cpp_heap())->sweeper().IsSweepingInProgress());
7532  }
7533 
7534  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
7535  mode == SweepingForcedFinalizationMode::kUnifiedHeap || !cpp_heap(),
7536  !tracer()->IsSweepingInProgress());
7537 
7538  if (v8_flags.external_memory_accounted_in_global_limit) {
7539  if (!using_initial_limit()) {
7540  auto new_limits = ComputeNewAllocationLimits(this);
7541  SetOldGenerationAndGlobalAllocationLimit(
7542  new_limits.old_generation_allocation_limit,
7543  new_limits.global_allocation_limit);
7544  }
7545  }
7546 }
7547 
7548 void Heap::EnsureQuarantinedPagesSweepingCompleted() {
7549  if (v8_flags.minor_ms) {
7550  return;
7551  }
7552  scavenger_collector_->CompleteSweepingQuarantinedPagesIfNeeded();
7553 }
7554 
7555 void Heap::EnsureYoungSweepingCompleted() {
7556  CompleteArrayBufferSweeping(this);
7557 
7558  EnsureQuarantinedPagesSweepingCompleted();
7559 
7560  if (!sweeper()->minor_sweeping_in_progress()) return;
7561  DCHECK(!v8_flags.sticky_mark_bits);
7562 
7563  TRACE_GC_EPOCH_WITH_FLOW(
7564  tracer(), GCTracer::Scope::MINOR_MS_COMPLETE_SWEEPING, ThreadKind::kMain,
7565  sweeper_->GetTraceIdForFlowEvent(
7566  GCTracer::Scope::MINOR_MS_COMPLETE_SWEEPING),
7567  TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_IN);
7568 
7569  sweeper()->EnsureMinorCompleted();
7570  paged_new_space()->paged_space()->RefillFreeList();
7571 
7572  tracer()->NotifyYoungSweepingCompletedAndStopCycleIfFinished();
7573 }
7574 
7575 void Heap::NotifyLoadingStarted() {
7576  update_allocation_limits_after_loading_ = true;
7577  double now_ms = MonotonicallyIncreasingTimeInMs();
7578  DCHECK_NE(now_ms, kLoadTimeNotLoading);
7579  load_start_time_ms_.store(now_ms, std::memory_order_relaxed);
7580 }
7581 
7582 void Heap::NotifyLoadingEnded() {
7583  load_start_time_ms_.store(kLoadTimeNotLoading, std::memory_order_relaxed);
7584  RecomputeLimitsAfterLoadingIfNeeded();
7585  if (auto* job = incremental_marking()->incremental_marking_job()) {
7586  // The task will start incremental marking (if needed not already started)
7587  // and advance marking if incremental marking is active.
7588  job->ScheduleTask(TaskPriority::kUserVisible);
7589  }
7590 }
7591 
7592 int Heap::NextScriptId() {
7593  FullObjectSlot last_script_id_slot(&roots_table()[RootIndex::kLastScriptId]);
7594  Tagged<Smi> last_id = Cast<Smi>(last_script_id_slot.Relaxed_Load());
7595  Tagged<Smi> new_id, last_id_before_cas;
7596  do {
7597  if (last_id.value() == Smi::kMaxValue) {
7598  static_assert(v8::UnboundScript::kNoScriptId == 0);
7599  new_id = Smi::FromInt(1);
7600  } else {
7601  new_id = Smi::FromInt(last_id.value() + 1);
7602  }
7603 
7604  // CAS returns the old value on success, and the current value in the slot
7605  // on failure. Therefore, we want to break if the returned value matches the
7606  // old value (last_id), and keep looping (with the new last_id value) if it
7607  // doesn't.
7608  last_id_before_cas = last_id;
7609  last_id =
7610  Cast<Smi>(last_script_id_slot.Relaxed_CompareAndSwap(last_id, new_id));
7611  } while (last_id != last_id_before_cas);
7612 
7613  return new_id.value();
7614 }
7615 
7616 int Heap::NextDebuggingId() {
7617  int last_id = last_debugging_id().value();
7618  if (last_id == DebugInfo::DebuggingIdBits::kMax) {
7619  last_id = DebugInfo::kNoDebuggingId;
7620  }
7621  last_id++;
7622  set_last_debugging_id(Smi::FromInt(last_id));
7623  return last_id;
7624 }
7625 
7626 int Heap::NextStackTraceId() {
7627  int last_id = last_stack_trace_id().value();
7628  if (last_id == Smi::kMaxValue) {
7629  last_id = 0;
7630  }
7631  last_id++;
7632  set_last_stack_trace_id(Smi::FromInt(last_id));
7633  return last_id;
7634 }

7712 ConservativePinningScope::ConservativePinningScope(Heap* heap) : heap_(heap) {
7713  DCHECK(::heap::base::Stack::IsOnCurrentStack(this));
7714  DCHECK(!heap_->selective_stack_scan_start_address_.has_value());
7715  // `frame_address` should be higher than `this`, but we observed that this
7716  // may not hold in some cases (e.g. due to missing inlining or unexpected
7717  // frame layouts). In such cases, we scan the stack either from the last
7718  // c_entry_fp or the whole stack.
7719  const Address c_entry_fp = *heap_->isolate()->c_entry_fp_address();
7720  const void* frame_address =
7721  (c_entry_fp == kNullAddress)
7722  ? static_cast<void*>(v8::base::Stack::GetStackStart())
7723  : reinterpret_cast<const void*>(c_entry_fp);
7724  // The stack segment covered by this scope should include the scope itself.
7725  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(frame_address);
7726  DCHECK_LE(this, frame_address);
7727  DCHECK(::heap::base::Stack::IsOnCurrentStack(frame_address));
7728  heap_->selective_stack_scan_start_address_ = frame_address;
7729 }
7730 ConservativePinningScope::~ConservativePinningScope() {
7731  DCHECK(heap_->selective_stack_scan_start_address_.has_value());
7732  heap_->selective_stack_scan_start_address_.reset();
7733 }
